[[lt:Kastelo mokykla]]

The '''Czech-Slovak Protective Society''' (CSPS), which became the '''Czecho Slovakian Association''', was an organization supporting the welfare of [[Czech American|Czech]] and [[Slovak American|Slovak]] immigrants to the [[United States]]. The Czech-Slovak Protective Society started as an insurance services organization.<ref name=sokol>{{cite news|url=http://minnesota.publicradio.org/display/web/2008/04/01/sokol/ |title=Sokol keeps Czech-Slovak heritage alive |author=William Wilcoxen, |publisher=Minnesota Public Radio |date=April 2, 2008}}</ref>
==History== The CSPS was founded in [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]], in 1854, and, like other immigrant societies, began by offering a kind of insurance program, which provided for members when they were ill and covered funeral expenses.<ref name=nrhpdoc-saint-paul>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=77000763}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: C.S.P.S. Hall / Czech Hall|publisher=[[National Park Service]]|accessdate=2016-06-25|author=Marlin L. Heise |date=July 16, 1976}} with {{NRHP url|id=77000763|photos=y|title=three photos}}</ref> It was the "largest [[Bohemian]] fraternal organization".<ref name=gbook>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2JbU1d9Xil0C&pg=PA182&lpg=PA182&dq=Czech-Slovak+Protective+Society&source=bl&ots=vKaamNist_&sig=EoI31NS-ZIXFbVE8XSA06cpHpVE&hl=en&ei=seurTPedPIT48AaS_92xCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CDQQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=Czech-Slovak%20Protective%20Society&f=false |title=Ethnic Chicago: a multicultural portrait |author=Melvin G. Holli, Peter d'Alroy Jones|year=1995}}</ref>{{rp|182}}
<!--- following needs editing to provide quoting or rewording ---> The Czecho-Slovak Protective Society, headquartered in St. Louis, Missouri, joined in organizing the '''Czechoslovak Society of America''' in 1933. That organization, based in [[Berwyn, Illinois]] changed its name to [[CSA Fraternal Life]] in 1982.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nfcanet.org/pdf/mergers_changes.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100215125057/http://www.nfcanet.org/pdf/mergers_changes.pdf |archivedate=2010-02-15 |df= }}</ref>
<!--- following needs editing to provide quoting or rewording ---> Č.S.P.S. stands for "Česko-Slovenský Podporující Spolek" (Czech-Slovak Protective Society). These lodges were the forerunner of the (Západní Česko-Bratrská Jednota, or Western Bohemian Fraternal Association). Both associations offered a type of insurance for the Czech people. The association later became known as the [[Western Fraternal Life Association]].<ref>[http://www.unl.edu/Czechheritage/Margie_sobotka.shtml Our Czech Heritage]</ref>
{{anchor|List of C.S.P.S. buildings}} ==Local lodges== [[File:CSPS Hall.jpg|right|thumb|[[C.S.P.S. Hall (Saint Paul, Minnesota)]]]]
*The first CSPS lodge in Cedar Rapids, Iowa, was started in 1879, and two more were started by 1882. The [[C.S.P.S. Hall (Cedar Rapids, Iowa)]], was built during 1890-91 and expanded twice in the next two decades. It is NRHP-listed in 1978.<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref><ref name=nrhpdoc-cedar-rapids>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=78001237}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: C.S.P.S. Hall |publisher=[[National Park Service]]|accessdate=2016-06-25|author=Steve Altheide |date=1978}} with {{NRHP url|id=78001237|photos=y|title= photo from 1977}}</ref>{{rp|}} *The [[Grand Lodge Č.S.P.S. of Baltimore]] was founded in 1880. The associated [[Bohemian National Cemetery (Baltimore, Maryland)|Bohemian National Cemetery]], in Baltimore, Maryland, was started in 1884, and is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] (NRHP). *The C.S.P.S. of Iowa City, Iowa, was organized in 1882 and built its [[Czecho Slovakian Association Hall]] in 1900. The hall was listed on the NRHP in 1975.<ref name=nris/><ref name=nrhpdoc-iowa-city>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=76000775}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Czecho Slovakian Association Hall / The Preucil School of Music |publisher=[[National Park Service]]|accessdate=2016-06-25 |author= William Preucil |date=August 1975}} with {{NRHP url|id=76000775|photos=y|title=photo from 1975}}</ref> *The C.S.P.S. of Saint Paul, Minnesota built [[C.S.P.S. Hall (Saint Paul, Minnesota)|its C.S.P.S. hall]] in 1887; it is also NRHP-listed.<ref name=nrhpdoc-saint-paul/><ref name=nris/> *[[Narodni Sin]], Edwardsville, Illinois, built 1906, NRHP-listed *[[Czech Hall]], Yukon, Oklahoma, built 1925, NRHP-listed<ref name=nris/> *[[CSPS Lodge-Griesser Bakery]], built 1890, in Bryan, Texas, NRHP-listed
