{{italic title}} '''''Dro''''' ({{lang-ka|დრო}}, 'Time') was a daily [[Georgian language]] [[bolshevik]] newspaper, published in [[Tbilisi]] from March 24, 1907 to April 28, 1907. The editor of ''Dro'' was [[Ilya Tsivtsivadze]]. Amongst the people involved in the newspaper were [[Joseph Stalin]], [[M. G. Tskhakaya]] and [[M. Davitashvili]]. The newspaper was published several articles of [[Lenin]]. ''Dro'' was central in mobilizing the bolshevik positions in the Caucasus ahead of the [[5th Congress of the Russian Social Democratic Labour Party]]. After 31 editions, ''Dro'' was closed down by state authorities.<ref>[[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]]: [http://bse.sci-lib.com/article033529.html «Дро»]</ref>
