{{Infobox museum | name = Supa Ngwao Museum | native_name = Francistown Museum | native_name_lang = [[Setswana]] | image = Supa Ngwao Museum (Francistown Botswana).jpg | caption = Supa Ngwao Museum in [[Francistown]], [[Botswana]] | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|21|10|25|S|27|30|45|E|region:BW-NE|display=inline}}
| established = 1986 | dissolved = | location = [[Francistown]] , [[Botswana]] | type = | collection = [[History of Botswana]] | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | network = | website = }}
The '''Supa Ngwao Museum'''{{Pronunciation-needed}} is located in the [[Francistown]] city in [[Botswana]].<ref name="Francistown museum">{{cite web |url=http://trickleout.net/index.php/directory-pilot/botswana/supa-ngwao-museum-centre |title=About supa ngwao |work=Francistown Museum|accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref> It is a public institution dedicated to human history's, art and culture. The museum was established in the year 1986, largely to preserve the historical information about the [[Francistown]] city and other places around it in the northern region. Supa Ngwao museum is responsible for showcasing the history and culture of [[Kalanga people]]. There are three sections at the Supa museum including the museum, information center and the craft shop.{{citation needed|date=September 2017}}
==History== Supa Ngwao museum was first established as a mobile museum with the main aim of preserving, teaching about the human history's, arts and culture of the [[Kalanga people]] and people living in northern Botswana.{{citation needed|date=September 2017}}
